properties.text: You can change character through the local variable of the object "Values_Player" or through the action "Values_Player -> Set value"
Use the grid to align objects during insertion
don't forget to align the image points
a more convenient way to align image points
after alignment, apply for all animations
but remember, this is not always necessary, but only when the sprite "twitches"
you can also configure the interface and the like in the "GlobalsValues" object
P.S you can also click 2 times on a variable to see a comment for it and find out what it is responsible for
If you want to delete an object COMPLETELY from the project, then you should delete it through the objects panel, if you delete an object on the stage, it will remain in the game files
If you want to duplicate the layout, keep in mind that you need to create a separate event sheet for the duplicated layout, otherwise it will use the event sheet of the previous layout
(the numbers show how to duplicate the layout correctly)
